New Algorithm Description: In the new algorithm, the scores for the bins will be calculated by taking the product of the logarithm of the bin capacity and the inverse of the difference between the bin capacity and the item size, then normalizing the scores by dividing them by the sum of all scores and multiplying them by the logarithm of their original values.

import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    # Calculate the scores for the bins
    difference = bins - item
    scores = np.log(bins) * (1 / difference)
    normalized_scores = (scores / np.sum(scores)) * np.log(scores)
    
    return scores
